fields.description:
There are 2 ways the job name for each entry in the summary tables is determined:

* Job name parsed from the log file
* Job name provided by the webhook notification

Sometimes, the job name derived from the log file is overwriting the job name provided by the webhook.

Suggested fix:
Use two columns in DB {{job_name}} and {{log_job_name}}. From the log parsing populate the {{log_job_name}}. From the webhook notification populate the {{job_name}}. While displaying on UI - use {{job_name}} if it is populated else use {{log_job_name}}
fields.summary: Job name that shows up on UI is not the job name from the orchestrator (tidal)
